Acumatica ERP gives your company a complete set of business software applications that your users can use anytime, from anywhere, by using virtually any device. On the other hand, only employees of your company can use the applications provided as part of Acumatica ERP. The way your employees have been able to communicate with your customers is manual and based on emails, phone calls, and postal mail.{br}
With the many advancements in technology, customers expect to have all the information they need from your company at their fingertips. Most of the interaction between you and your customers should be online, automated, always available, and provided as self-service.{br}
The Acumatica Self-Service Portal provides a solution for you to more efficiently work and communicate with your customers. Self-Service Portal is specifically designed to be the site where your customers can view all the relevant information about their interactions with you as a vendor and perform needed activities online.{br}{TOC} ==Customer Self-Service Capability== By using Self-Service Portal, your customers can access their account information, create and manage support cases, and create and track online orders—all without picking up the phone or sending an email. All of these services are available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. ==Self-Update of Customer Information== By using Self-Service Portal, customers can view and promptly update their company address and contact information, to keep the data in the system up to date at all times. You can view the updated information about the customer business account on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_30_00|Business Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR303000|CR303000]) form. ==Financial Overview== Within the Self-Service Portal, customers have the ability to see all historical documents, balances, due dates, payments received, and amount due. ==Case Management== Customers can use Self-Service Portal to submit new cases, which seamlessly flow into Acumatica ERP. You can view the new cases by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_60_00|Cases] ([~/?ScreenId=CR306000|CR306000]) form. The customers can view the cases they submitted, track the statuses of these cases, provide additional information when required, and reopen closed cases. ((({S:Warn}You can set up a period during which users can reopen the case by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_60_00|Case Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=CR206000|CR206000]) form. ))) For more information, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CR__MNG_Cases|Managing Cases]. ==Online Ordering== With online ordering in Acumatica Self-Service Portal, you give your customers access to the products you sell. You use your Acumatica ERP instance to build the catalog and manage the product descriptions and images. {br}
Your customers can use Self-Service Portal to browse the list of available items, view item details, and then order the items online. The sales order is automatically generated and you can further process it. The customer tracks the status of the order and the shipments online. Also, the customer can view the invoice after you release the document. For more information, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__mng_Online_Ordering|Managing Online Orders].((({S:Warn}This feature is inaccessible if the ''Inventory and Order Management'' group of features is disabled. ))) ==Delegated User Management== You can assign a user or multiple users of each customer as delegated administrators and give these users the rights to add new contacts or users to the customer&rsquo;s business account by using Self-Service Portal. The delegated administrators can also assign the users one or more of the roles you have provided. All the added contacts are immediately visible on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR302000|CR302000]) form in Acumatica ERP. ==Document Sharing== Self-Service Portal provides a secure location to share with customers important content, such as marketing and informational documents, as well as corporate policies—all without the need to build a separate webpage. For more information, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__mng_Wiki_Overview|Managing Self-Service Portal Wikis]. ==Knowledge Base== The Knowledge Base (KB) wiki is designed to host support references, such as information on specific solutions, frequently asked questions (FAQ), and common troubleshooting issues and their resolutions. The KB articles, created and published by your company&rsquo;s support professionals, ensure that your customers can search the knowledge base to find answers to their questions whenever they want. For more information, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__mng_Wiki_Overview|Managing Self-Service Portal Wikis]. ==Localization== You can localize the user interface of Self-Service Portal and wiki articles to multiple languages. You can translate the strings of the application&rsquo;s user interface directly in the application or by exporting the application strings to a third-party product, performing the translation in that product, and importing the translated strings back. For details, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__mng_Translation|Managing Localization of Self-Service Portal]. ==Customization of the User Interface== In Acumatica ERP, you can flexibly customize the user interface (in particular, main menu items and workspace links) that all users will see so that it fits the business processes of your organization. Your customization of the user interface will make it easier for users to find and begin working with required forms, speeding document processing in the system. For example, you can add generic inquiry forms or dashboards to a Self-Service Portal site map on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_05_21|Portal Map] ([~/?ScreenId=SM200521|SM200521]) form, so that the forms are available for quick access. For details, see [HelpRoot_Administration\AS__mng_User_Interface_Configuration|Customizing the User Interface].

Acumatica Self-Service Portal provides tools that you can use to configure and maintain your Self-Service Portal instance. This functionality has been grouped under the Self-Service Portal Configuration suite into two modules: Administrator and Knowledge Base Management.{br}
In this topic, you will find information on the modules of the Configuration suite of Self-Service Portal and the Acumatica ERP roles used to administer Self-Service Portal.{br}{TOC} ==Administrator Module== By using the Administrator module of the Self-Service Portal Configuration suite, you can license your Self-Service Portal instance, select the default settings, configure access to the functionality, set up single sign-on (SSO) with the supported identity providers, and customize your Self-Service Portal instance. {br}
To access the Administrator module of the Configuration suite, you must sign in to your Self-Service Portal instance with the user account that is a member of the ''Administrator'' or ''Portal Admin'' role. ==Knowledge Base Management Module== You use the Knowledge Base Management module of the Self-Service Portal Configuration suite to configure the Self-Service Portal wikis, including the predefined and custom wikis. For more information, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__mng_Wiki_Overview|Managing Self-Service Portal Wikis]. ==Roles for Self-Service Portal Management== In Acumatica ERP, you configure all access including access to the wiki, by using roles. For the internal users to perform configuration and management tasks on Self-Service Portal, the users must have sufficient access rights to Self-Service Portal. Generally, the users who work with Self-Service Portal must have the following access rights:[anchor|#ul_ald_xs4_ds] *To configure and manage the Self-Service Portal instance, you assign users ''Portal Admin'' role. This role has been specifically designed to allow users to configure and manage Self-Service Portal by using the Administrator module. *:((({S:Warn}A user with this role assigned will be able to use the Configuration suite and view the wikis (including Help wiki) but won&rsquo;t be able to use other Self-Service Portal suites. ))) *To initially configure the Self-Service Portal instance, you can assign users the ''Administrator'' role. A user with the ''Administrator'' role has full access to all system objects. *:((({S:Warn} We recommend that you assign users to this role only during initial Self-Service Portal setup. Then use the role only in extraordinary cases. ))) *To configure and manage the Self-Service Portal wikis and wiki articles, you assign users one or multiple roles that give access to wiki management. You can use the predefined ''Wiki Admin'' and ''Wiki Author'' roles or configure your own custom roles.
For more information on Acumatica ERP roles, see [HelpRoot_Administration\SA_Managing_User_Access_Mapref|Managing User Access].

Before your users can use the Self-Service Portal instance that you have installed, you have to configure the instance view and functionality.{br}
