Acumatica Self-Service Portal is a special site designed to give your customers limited access to your Acumatica ERP instance. To let a contact access your Self-Service Portal instance, you add a user account to the contact in Acumatica ERP.{br}{TOC} ==Portal User Role== Acumatica ERP provides a built-in role, ''Portal User'', that may have access to Self-Service Portal. A user with this role assigned can sign in to Self-Service Portal and review the information pertaining to the business account that is associated with the contact account of the user, including:[anchor|#ul_mjw_hh5_wp] *The company profile: The user can view and edit the company&rsquo;s contact information and address. *Contacts: The user can add, delete, and manage the contacts within the organization. *Contracts with the organization: The user can view the contracts with the organization *The financial documents associated with the company: The user can view and print the documents, such as the statement history, the invoices, and the current balance and prepayment balance.
You can change the default role settings by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_25|Access Rights by Role] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201025|SM201025]) form of the Configuration suite of Self-Service Portal. For more information about roles, see [HelpRoot_Administration\User_Roles_Mapref|Configuring User Roles]. ==External User Types== In Acumatica ERP, user types define which entity type (employee or contact) and which roles can be associated with the user accounts. {br}
User types for portal users must have the ''contact'' linked entity type selected and include the ''Portal User'' role in the role set. Also, you can configure contact-related user types to delegate the rights to create and manage new users to external users. {br}
For more information, see [HelpRoot_Administration\SA_Managing_User_Access_User_Types_Usage_Concept|User Access: Linked Entity and User Type]. ==User Accounts for Contacts== You can add a user account to a contact account in one of the following ways:[anchor|#ul_bv4_1y1_5p] *By using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR302000|CR302000]) form to open the contact for editing, and then adding the user account information on the '''User Info''' tab *By using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_10|Users] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201010|SM201010]) form to create a user account and linking it with a contact account
When you create a user account, you must select a contact-related user type and assign the user the ''Portal User'' role. For detailed procedure, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\US__how_Add_External_User|To Add a User Account for a Contact ]. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\US__how_Add_External_User|To Add a User Account for a Contact ] *[HelpRoot_Administration\SA_Managing_User_Access_User_Types_Usage_Concept|User Access: Linked Entity and User Type] *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR302000|CR302000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_25|Access Rights by Role] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201025|SM201025]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_10|Users] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201010|SM201010])

With online ordering on Acumatica Self-Service Portal, you provide your customers with access to the products you sell. You use your Acumatica ERP instance to form the catalog and manage the product descriptions and images. Your customers can then use Self-Service Portal to browse the catalog and place orders online.{br}{TOC} ==Overall Configuration Process== You form the catalog that is to be available to your customers on the Self-Service Portal directly from your Acumatica ERP instance by using the functionality of the Inventory module. By assigning an item sales category to an inventory item, you both categorize the item and include the item in the online catalog. For more information on managing inventory items, see the [HelpRoot_InvMgmt\IN_00_00_00|Inventory Management] part of the Acumatica ERP Inventory Management Guide.{br}
Managing the online catalog includes the following tasks, which you perform by using your Acumatica ERP instance:[anchor|#ol_vx2_lsy_vp] #Configuring inventory items before you present the items in the online catalog, including adding extended descriptions for the items and uploading item images #Forming the catalog structure by adding, deleting, and organizing sales categories #Assigning sales categories to inventory items, thus adding the inventory items to the catalog #:((({S:Warn}Inventory items without a sales category assigned do not appear in the catalog. )))
==Inventory Item Descriptions and Images== In Acumatica ERP, every inventory item, both stock and non-stock, has a basic set of item properties. These properties include the item’s identifier, description, images, price, cost, units of measure, default warehouse, and default vendor information. Your customers can view the descriptions and images you provide for your inventory items. ((({S:Warn}On Self-Service Portal, the images you provide in the descriptions are displayed only in the '''Description''' section. To make the images available in the '''Images''' section, you have to add images to the images collection of the inventory item. ))) For details on adding descriptions and images to inventory items, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\IN__how_Add_Item_Description|To Add Descriptions and Images to Inventory Items]. ==Item Sales Categories== The hierarchy of sales categories form the catalog structure. You add new categories and subcategories, and move and delete old ones to make the catalog structure easy to manage and to navigate. For detailed procedures on adding, deleting, and managing sales categories, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\IN__how_OnlineOrder_Add_sales_Category|To Add a New Item Sales Category] and [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\IN__how_OnlineOrder_Manage_Sales_Categories|To Organize Item Sales Categories].{br}
You assign your inventory items the sales categories to form the online catalog. You can add items to a sales category one by one, in bulk by item class, or all items specified in the system, as described in [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\IN__how_Online_Order_Add_to_Catalog|To Add Inventory Items to the Catalog]. Also, you can delete items from the sales categories, as described in [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\IN__how_OnlineOrder_Delete_from_Catalog|To Remove an Item from the Catalog]. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\IN__how_OnlineOrder_Add_sales_Category|To Add a New Item Sales Category] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\IN__how_Add_Item_Description|To Add Descriptions and Images to Inventory Items] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\IN__how_OnlineOrder_Manage_Sales_Categories|To Organize Item Sales Categories] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\IN__how_Online_Order_Add_to_Catalog|To Add Inventory Items to the Catalog] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\IN__how_OnlineOrder_Delete_from_Catalog|To Remove an Item from the Catalog]

The Orders suite of the Acumatica Self-Service                         Portal gives your customers the ability to order products online: They can browse the list of products, view the detailed product information, place orders, and monitor their progress. This topic describes the general steps in online order processing and the flow of data between your Self-Service Portal and Acumatica ERP instances. The specific procedures of this process depend on your company&rsquo;s requirements.{br}{TOC}
==Using the Catalog==
In Acumatica ERP, you form the catalog and provide product descriptions and images. Your customer signs in to the Self-Service Portal instance and browses the catalog. For every item in the catalog, the customer can see the description, images, price, and availability in different warehouses. 
==Placing Orders==
After your customer decides which items to purchase, the customer does the following:[anchor|#ol_tr2_vg1_yp]
#Places an order through Self-Service Portal, selecting the items to buy and specifying the item quantities
#Specifies shipping instructions, including the warehouses the items should be shipped from, the desired delivery date, the shipping location, and the carrier to be used for shipping the ordered goods
#Prints the order

==Processing Orders==
This order immediately becomes available on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form of your Acumatica ERP instance, thus helping you plan the fulfillment of the order.{br}

The type of the generated order depends on the online ordering configuration of Self-Service Portal. For more information, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__con_Online_Ordering_Configuration|Prior Self-Service Portal Configuration].{br}

You process the order in accordance with your company&rsquo;s policy and the customer&rsquo;s contract; the order status is changed accordingly with each processing step. The customer can monitor the changes in the order status through Self-Service Portal. {br}

For more information on sales orders, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO_00_00_00|Order Management].
==Processing Shipments==
You directly create a shipment document for a particular sales order or a consolidated shipment for multiple sales orders of the same customer in Acumatica ERP. Then you process the shipment in accordance with your company&rsquo;s policy and the customer&rsquo;s contract; the shipment status is changed accordingly with each processing step.{br}

Your customer can see all shipments associated with a particular order, print the shipping documents, and track shipping statuses through Self-Service Portal.{br}

For more information on shipments, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Shipments|Processing Partial Shipments].
==Processing Invoices==
All the invoices you generate in Acumatica ERP for a customer become available in Self-Service Portal for this customer. ((({S:Warn}In Self-Service Portal, the invoices are not directly associated with the orders.
)))

With Acumatica Self-Service Portal, you can give your customers the ability to submit new cases, change the case priority, enter additional information, get updates on the case status by email, check the case for updates, and view responses to the case.{br}
In this topic, you will find information on case management and the flow of data between your Self-Service Portal and Acumatica ERP instances.{br}
For more information on case management in Acumatica ERP, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CR__MNG_Cases|Managing Cases].{br}{TOC} ==Case Settings in Acumatica ERP== With Self-Service Portal, your customers take part of the case processing: They can submit new cases, add new information to the cases, and then close the resolved cases. The customer&rsquo;s input is seamlessly incorporated into the case processing. In addition to your general case processing, you only have to have case classes that can be used to submit cases through Self-Service Portal.((({S:Hint}You must configure at least one case class through Self-Service Portal (that is, a case class with the '''Internal''' check box cleared on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_60_00|Case Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=CR206000|CR206000]) form). ))) The case management setup in Acumatica ERP is described in detail in [HelpRoot_CRM\CR__MNG_Cases|Managing Cases]. ==Case Settings in Self-Service Portal== You select the following default settings for Self-Service Portal:[anchor|#ul_p1z_5yb_xp] *The default case class *The default case priority
The customers can change the defaults when they submit new cases.{br}
The detailed procedure is described in [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Cases_Configuration|To Set Up Defaults for Case Management on Self-Service Portal]. ==Case Visibility on Self-Service Portal== A case may be visible on Self-Service Portal only if the following conditions are met:[anchor|#_364ddf7e-ac26-4ba4-9812-aebbfe896456] *The case belongs to a case class with the '''Internal''' check box cleared on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_60_00|Case Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=CR206000|CR206000]) form. *If the case is assigned to an employee, the contact that is linked to the employee belongs to a contact class with the '''Internal''' check box cleared on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_50_00|Contact Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=CR205000|CR205000]) form.
==Case Processing== Case processing starts when a customer submits a new case. The new case immediately becomes available in Acumatica ERP, where you process it according to your company&rsquo;s workflow. {br}
Customers can track cases by the changes in the case status, which can be any of the following:[anchor|#ul_rl4_z1c_xp] *''New'': The customer submitted a new case. *''Open'': The case is processed. *:((({S:Warn}When a case is resolved and the customer closes it, the case status is set to ''Open'' with the reason ''Pending Closure''. You must add any required information to the case and close the case yourself. ))) *''Pending Customer'': The case requires customer input; the details are available in the case details. *''Closed'': The case is resolved and closed.
When the case status is changed, the customer gets a email notification. ==Case Notifications== To help case owners monitor the cases created by user through Self-Service Portal, you can set up notifications on changes in such cases. With the notification enabled, case owners get emails when customers make changes in case records on Self-Service Portal. For details on setting up notifications on changes in cases, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Notifications_on_cases|To Set Up Notifications About Comments in Cases]. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_CRM\CR__MNG_Cases|Managing Cases] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Cases_Configuration|To Set Up Defaults for Case Management on Self-Service Portal] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Notifications_on_cases|To Set Up Notifications About Comments in Cases]

With Acumatica Self-Service Portal wikis, you can share content with your customers, including marketing and informational materials, frequently asked questions (FAQ), and other information you want to give your customers easy access to. Typically, Self-Service Portal wikis are displayed in the Self-Service Portal instance and hidden in the corresponding Acumatica ERP instance. You can perform all tasks related to Self-Service Portal wikis by using the Knowledge Base Management module of the Self-Service Portal Configuration suite.{br}
This topic describes the main details of configuring, managing, adding content, and maintaining Self-Service Portal wikis.{br}
For more information on wikis in Acumatica ERP, see [HelpRoot_Administration\SM__con_Wiki_Management|Wiki Overview].{br}{TOC} ==Process of Managing Self-Service Portal Wikis== The process of managing Self-Service Portal wikis includes the following tasks:[anchor|#_608d46bc-1548-428e-afa8-070ac7d80004] *''Creating wikis'': You can add a new wiki when you want to publish information specific to the business processes of your organization for users of the Self-Service Portal. Otherwise, you can add articles in a predefined wiki. (For information on predefined Self-Service Portal wikis, see [[#_c0700d69-2e38-41e1-b639-7cbf33f8c9d9|Predefined Wikis].) You can add wikis and configure access to wikis down to the wiki article level by using the forms in the Knowledge Base Management module of the Self-Service Portal Configuration suite. For details about adding a wiki, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Add_new_wiki_from_ERP|To Create a Wiki in Self-Service Portal]. *''Managing wiki content'': You can add and publish new articles, edit existing articles, and remove outdated wiki articles. For more information on wiki content management tasks, see [HelpRoot_Administration\DM__mng_Wiki_How_To|Wiki Content Procedures]. *''Providing access rights to wikis'': You can set up access rights for users to view entire wikis or certain wiki articles and to edit wiki content. For more information, see [HelpRoot_Administration\SM__con_Wiki_Access_Setup|Wiki Access Management]. *''Configuring the predefined Welcome article'': You can edit the Welcome article when you want to place important information for portal users there. The Welcome article is used as the default Self-Service Portal home page. For details, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__How_Editing_Home_page|To Configure the Default Self-Service Portal Welcome Page]. *''Using a wiki as a home page'': You can replace the Self-Service Portal home page with a selected wiki page when information on this page should be at hand for most of portal users. For more information, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__mng_Home_Page|Managing the Self-Service Portal Home Page]. *''Locating wiki on both Self-Service Portal and Acumatica ERP'': You can configure a wiki that was created in Acumatica ERP to be visible on Self-Service Portal when you need particular articles to be visible to external users. For details, see [[#_d3a03957-53e4-4c26-a36c-1a0f1bd673ab|Visibility in of a Wiki Article Created in]. [anchor|#_c0700d69-2e38-41e1-b639-7cbf33f8c9d9] ==Predefined Self-Service Portal Wikis== By default, Self-Service Portal includes the Self-Service Portal Guide, the Home page wiki, and the Knowledge Base wiki. {br}
The Self-Service Portal Guide provides an overview of the Self-Service Portal functionality and forms, the website user interface, and the navigation options provided specifically for customers. ((({S:Hint}We strongly recommend that you restrict the ability to modify this guide. ))) The Self-Service Portal Home Page wiki is a service wiki; it contains the Welcome article that is used as the default Self-Service Portal home page. By default, the Welcome article contains links to the most useful Self-Service Portal forms; you can edit the contents of the article. For details, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__How_Editing_Home_page|To Configure the Default Self-Service Portal Welcome Page].((({S:Warn}You can select another article or create a dashboard to be used as the Self-Service Portal home page. But if the selected article or dashboard becomes unavailable for any reason, the system reverts to the default wiki article. For more information, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__mng_Home_Page|Managing the Self-Service Portal Home Page]. ))) The Knowledge Base (KB) wiki is designed to host support references, such as information on specific solutions, frequently asked questions (FAQ), and common troubleshooting issues and their resolutions. The KB articles are to be created and published by your company&rsquo;s support professionals to ensure that your customers can search the knowledge base to find answers to their questions whenever they want.[anchor|#_d3a03957-53e4-4c26-a36c-1a0f1bd673ab] ==Visibility in Self-Service Portal of a Wiki Article Created in Acumatica ERP== You can create a wiki article in Acumatica ERP and display it on Self-Service Portal. For example, suppose that the support engineers of your organization have added a FAQ article in Acumatica ERP, and they want to publish it in the knowledge base on Self-Service Portal for partners as well. {br}
To make a wiki article created in Acumatica ERP visible on Self-Service Portal, you do the following:[anchor|#_2da12317-1682-4ca2-82a5-f15a4e0ecf04] #Select the wiki that contains the article you want to display on Self-Service Portal. #Add the wiki to the Self-Service Portal site map. #Set up the access rights to the wiki and the article for users who may need to view them during their work.
For the detailed procedure, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Share_Portal_Wiki_Article_with_ERP|To Make a Wiki Article Visible in Self-Service Portal]. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_Administration\DM__mng_Wiki_How_To|Wiki Content Procedures] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__mng_Wiki_Overview|Managing Self-Service Portal Wikis] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__mng_Home_Page|Managing the Self-Service Portal Home Page] *[HelpRoot_Administration\SM__con_Wiki_Management|Wiki Overview] *[HelpRoot_Administration\SM__con_Wiki_Access_Setup|Wiki Access Management] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Add_new_wiki_from_ERP|To Create a Wiki in Self-Service Portal] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__How_Editing_Home_page|To Configure the Default Self-Service Portal Welcome Page] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Share_Portal_Wiki_Article_with_ERP|To Make a Wiki Article Visible in Self-Service Portal]

The Self-Service Portal home page is a wiki article located in the predefined Portal Site wiki. For more information, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__con_Portal_wiki_managementi|Management of Self-Service Portal Wikis].{br}
Depending on your system configuration, you can use one the following options to customize the contents of the page:[anchor|#ul_mpk_jvb_gr] *If you use the default home page as the home page of your Self-Service Portal instance, open the home page and edit the contents of the wiki article. For more information, see [HelpRoot_Administration\DM__mng_Wiki_How_To|Wiki Content Procedures]. *If you selected another article or dashboard to be used as the Self-Service Portal home page, perform the following general steps, which are described in more detail in the following section: *#Use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_20_05|Wiki] ([~/?ScreenId=SM202005|SM202005]) form to make the Portal Site wiki available for editing. *#Open the Self-Service Portal home page, and edit it as you do with any wiki article. *#Navigate to the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_20_05|Wiki] ([~/?ScreenId=SM202005|SM202005]) form, and hide the Portal Site wiki.
==To Configure the Default Self-Service Portal Welcome Page==[anchor|#ol_t5l_z53_2l] #To make the Portal Site wiki available for editing, do the following in your Self-Service Portal instance: ##Open the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_20_05|Wiki] ([~/?ScreenId=SM202005|SM202005]) form. ##In the '''ID''' box, select the ''Portal Site'' wiki. ##In the '''Site Map Location''' box, select ''Documentation'' to make the wiki available on the Self-Service Portal main menu. ##On the form toolbar, click '''Save'''. ##Reload the webpage in the browser to view the Portal Site wiki in the main menu. #Open and edit the Self-Service Portal home page as follows: ##On the '''Documentation''' tab, click '''Web&#95;Site'''. In the left pane, click '''Welcome'''. ##:The portal home page opens in the right pane. ##On the help toolbar, click '''Edit Current Article'''. ##Edit the contents of the article. ##On the form toolbar, click '''Save'''. #Hide the Portal Site wiki as follows: ##Open the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_20_05|Wiki] ([~/?ScreenId=SM202005|SM202005]) form. ##In the '''ID''' box, select the wiki that you want to hide from the main menu. ##In the '''Site Map Location''' box, delete the location. ##On the form toolbar, click '''Save''' to remove the wiki from the Self-Service Portal main menu. ##Reload the webpage in the browser to apply the changes to the site map of Self-Service Portal.

By default, the Self-Service Portal home page displays the default Welcome article of the Self-Service Portal Home Page wiki. To design the Self-Service Portal home page to meet your requirements, you can do one of the following:[anchor|#ol_n4t_4mc_gr] *Configure the dashboard to be used as the Self-Service Portal home page, as described in the [[#portal_dashboard|Configuring a Dashboard for the Home Page] section. *Select the wiki article to be used as the Self-Service Portal home page. *Edit the contents of the default Welcome article, as described in [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__How_Editing_Home_page|To Configure the Default Self-Service Portal Welcome Page].
If the selected article or dashboard becomes unavailable for any reason, the system will revert to the default Welcome article. {br}
To select the contents of the home page, you use the Portal Preferences (SP800000) form, as described in [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Home_page|To Select the Self-Service Portal Home Page].[anchor|#portal_dashboard] ==Configuring a Dashboard for the Home Page== In Acumatica ERP, a dashboard is a collection of widgets that are displayed on a single page. On Self-Service Portal, you can configure widgets on the Self-Service Portal inquiry forms by using the '''Dashboard''' menu of the form title bar. ((({S:Warn}For the dashboard to be displayed on the Self-Service Portal home page, you must select the company node as the default home page. ))) For more information about dashboards, see [HelpRoot_Interface\DB__mng_UIG_Dashboards|Dashboards]. ==Using a Wiki Article as the Self-Service Portal Home Page== You can use a wiki article as the Self-Service Portal home page. This article must belong to one of the Self-Service Portal wikis and must be published to be available to the users of your Self-Service Portal instance.

If your organization&rsquo;s customers and partners who use Acumatica Self-Service Portal speak different native languages, you can localize the user interface, user input, and wiki articles to these languages, as described in this chapter. ==In This Chapter==[anchor|#_02d7515c-904e-48f5-bff7-e9840430556a] {| class="checklist invisiblechecklist" | width="100%" |- | [anchor|#_d7f07f8b-2b10-45e9-97ca-2259a2903b31] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__con_Portal_Localization|Localization of Self-Service Portal] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__con_Translation_Process|Translation Process] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__con_Boxes_Multilanguage|Boxes that Display Translated Values]
