You can customize your Acumatica Self-Service Portal instance to make the it better suit your needs. If you have sufficient access rights, you can sign in to your Self-Service Portal instance and use the customization functionality to import and publish prepared customization projects.{br}
This topic describes the most pertinent points in Self-Service Portal customization. For more information on customizing Acumatica ERP, see the [HelpRoot_Dev_Customization\CG_About|Acumatica ERP Customization Guide]. ==Access Rights to Customization Functionality== To get the appropriate access needed for customizing Self-Service Portal, a user account must be granted the ''Customizer'' or ''Administrator'' role.((({S:Warn}We recommend that you assign users to this role only during initial system setup so they can define roles and enter users. Then use the role only in extraordinary cases. ))) For more information, see [HelpRoot_Dev_Customization\CG_GL_Stages_Role|To Assign the Customizer Role to a User Account] in Acumatica ERP Customization Guide. ==Customization Functionality on Self-Service Portal== After signing in to Self-Service Portal, you can view and access the following customization functionality, which you use to access other customization tools and facilities:[anchor|#ul_bj3_24l_4s] *The '''Customization''' menu on the form title bar *The [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_45_05|Customization Projects] ([~/?ScreenId=SM204505|SM204505]) form in the '''Administrator''' module of the Configuration suite
For more information, see [HelpRoot_Dev_Customization\CG_Platform| Acumatica Customization Platform] in Acumatica ERP Customization Guide.

In Acumatica Self-Service Portal, you can flexibly customize the user interface (in particular, main menu items and workspace links) all users will see to adjust it to the business processes of your organization. Your customization of the user interface will make it easier for users to find and begin working with required forms and speeding document processing on the portal.{br}
In this chapter, you will find information about the customization of the user interface that can be performed by users with the ''Administrator'' user role. ==In This Chapter==[anchor|#_7c559681-3ec5-4f9d-8d35-6a7bbd4bbb7c] {| class="checklist invisiblechecklist" | width="100%" |- | [anchor|#_4aba298d-11d3-4edd-9758-61b85961bc1a] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__con_User_Interface_Configuration|Customization of the User Interface]
| [anchor|#_304d9c04-219c-445a-9c01-27652a8aa2b3] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Add_Configure_Workspace|To Add and Configure a Workspace] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Add_Form_to_Workspace_Menu|To Add a Link to a Workspace] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Delete_Tile_from_Workpace_Menu|To Delete a Tile from a Workspace ] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Delete_Workspace|To Delete a Workspace] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Display_Hide_Forms_in_Workspace_Menu|To Display and Hide Forms in a Workspace] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Regroup_Items_in_Workspace_Menu|To Regroup Forms in a Workspace ] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Remove_Form_from_Workspace_Menu|To Remove a Form from a Workspace ] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Rename_Workspace|To Rename a Workspace] *[HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Reset_Menu_Settings|To Reset Menu Settings]
