The user interface of Self-Service Portal provides predefined user interface elements, such as workspaces and workspace tiles and links, which you can configure to adjust the user interface to the business processes of your organization. Because portal users can locate the forms they use most right away, they can perform their working tasks related to Self-Service Portal more easily.{br}
If your user account is assigned the ''Administrator'' or ''Portal Admin'' role, you customize the user interface in the special Menu Editing mode. The changes you make in this mode are applied to all users of Acumatica ERP.{br}
For the description of the user interface elements, see Self-Service Portal Interface in the Self-Service Portal Guide.{br}
In this topic, you will read about the capabilities in the system for customizing the user interface.{br}{TOC} ==Customization of the User Interface== You can customize the user interface as follows:[anchor|#_60b6fc42-9307-4431-a8e8-bb30a142e528] *Adjust the list of workspaces that are items on the main menu: You can keep in the user interface only the workspaces that correspond to the business processes of your organization. To perform this task, you can add new workspaces and populate them with items (tiles and links that provide access to forms), delete existing menu items for workspaces that do not comply with your business processes, and rename existing workspaces. For details, see [[#_ce60a6f0-56e6-44fb-b20f-3a0063d8ec39|Management of the Workspaces Listed on the Main Menu]. *Change the items of a workspace: You can customize a workspace so that only the items that portal users need to solve their tasks are displayed there. You can change the list of forms and dashboards in a workspace, regroup the links to forms in a workspace, reorder the links to forms in a category, remove unnecessary tiles and links to forms and dashboards from a workspace, and reorder tiles in a workspace. For more information, see [[#_c9acebc5-df19-4c66-8e09-4b123380478a|Management of Workspace Tiles and Links].
By using Menu Editing mode, you can customize the user interface in a variety of ways. To switch to this mode, on the main menu, you click the configuration menu button ([anchor|#_55f9375f-7fbb-4a10-a2f2-cdbb78a3972d][image:UserGuide/Images/Main_Menu_Dots.png|25px]) and then click '''Edit Menu'''.((({S:Warn}The '''Edit Menu''' item is available for only users with the ''Administrator'' or ''Portal Admin'' role. ))) If you customize the user interface in this mode and then decide to return the initial state of the main menu and all workspaces, you can reset the menu settings to default. Changes in the following menu elements will be reset: [anchor|#_2857f336-086f-46e8-934e-9315ddc8785c] *The list of workspaces that are items on the main menu and the '''More Items''' menu *Items in each workspace, including categories, tiles, and links to forms and dashboards *Items in quick menu of each workspace for all users of the system *Workspaces pinned to the main menu and unpinned from the main menu for all users of the system
For details, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Reset_Menu_Settings|To Reset Menu Settings].[anchor|#_ce60a6f0-56e6-44fb-b20f-3a0063d8ec39] ==Management of the Workspaces Listed on the Main Menu== The main menu is the primary navigation tool that you and portal use when you start working in Self-Service Portal. The system provides you with predefined workspaces list that is displayed in the main menu. The list of workspaces that a user sees by default is determined by the features enabled based on your Acumatica ERP license and the access rights of the user roles assigned to the particular user account.((({S:Warn}You must configure access rights for users to each form that belongs to a workspace. For details, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__mng_Access|Managing Access to Self-Service Portal]. ))) If the default list of workspaces (that is, the items on the main menu) does not correspond to the business processes of your organization, you can configure the list as follows:[anchor|#_8aa21377-c78c-41aa-b793-7188779a49df] *Rename existing workspaces: If a title of any existing workspace is not optimal for portal users, you can change the title to help users easily find the forms they need. For the steps you need to perform to rename a workspace, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Rename_Workspace|To Rename a Workspace]. *Delete existing workspaces: If a predefined workspace does not fit the business processes of your organization and will not be needed by portal users, you can completely delete it from the portal. When you delete a workspace, the system completely deletes tiles that belonged to the workspace, but forms and dashboards that belonged to the workspace remain in the system; you can add to other workspaces links to these forms and dashboards. For the procedure that describes how to delete a workspace, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Delete_Workspace|To Delete a Workspace]. *Add new workspaces: If your organization has a specific business process that requires forms and dashboards from different functional areas to be gathered on one menu for users&rsquo; convenience, you can create a custom workspace and pin it to the main menu panel. For details, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Add_Configure_Workspace|To Add and Configure a Workspace]. [anchor|#_c9acebc5-df19-4c66-8e09-4b123380478a] ==Management of Workspace Tiles and Links== Workspaces are used in the system to organize links to forms and dashboards in a way that is convenient to users. By default, each workspace contains tiles (buttons that provide users with quick access to frequently used forms) and links to forms and dashboards grouped by categories (such as '''Profiles''' and '''Preferences'''). Each organization has its own business processes and uses sets of Self-Service Portal forms and dashboards based on these processes.{br}
To make a workspace convenient for portal users, you can do the following:[anchor|#_ca8ce07c-2db6-4669-bf80-122b539f3ed4] *Change the default list of links to forms and dashboards displayed in a workspace: If you need different forms and dashboards to be displayed in a workspace, you can change the default list by showing the items that are hidden by default and hiding the items that are displayed by default. For details, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Display_Hide_Forms_in_Workspace_Menu|To Display and Hide Forms in a Workspace]. *Add new links to forms and dashboards to a workspace: If a link to a form and dashboard is not on a workspace by default but portal users want to have it in this workspace, you can add the required link to any Self-Service Portal form or dashboard to the workspace. For more information, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Add_Form_to_Workspace_Menu|To Add a Link to a Workspace]. *:((({S:Warn}If a link to a form is not added to any of workspaces you cannot find this form by using the '''Search''' box on the top pane of the Self-Service Portal screen. ))) *Regroup links to forms and dashboards in a workspace: If the default grouping of links to forms and dashboards in a workspace is inconvenient for portal users, you can move these links to other existing categories, or create a category that fits the terminology used by portal users. Changes to grouping settings affect only the workspace in which they are changed. For details, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Regroup_Items_in_Workspace_Menu|To Regroup Forms in a Workspace ]. *:((({S:Warn}If you need to move a link to an existing category, which is displayed in a workspace, in the Menu Editing mode, you can simply drag the link to the category. ))) *Reorder links to forms and dashboards in a category: In the Menu Editing mode, you can reorder links to forms and dashboards in a category by dragging each link to a necessary position. *Remove links to forms and dashboards from a workspace: If you are sure that users will not need a particular link to a form or dashboard in a workspace, you can remove this link from the workspace. (The form or dashboard will remain in the system.) For more information, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Remove_Form_from_Workspace_Menu|To Remove a Form from a Workspace ]. *Delete preconfigured tiles: If portal users do not use functions preconfigured in tiles, you can delete the tiles from a workspace to have more space in the workspace. For details, see [HelpRoot_SS_Portal_Admin\SP__how_Delete_Tile_from_Workpace_Menu|To Delete a Tile from a Workspace ]. *:((({S:Hint}After you delete a tile, you will be able to restore it only when restoring menu settings to default. ))) *Reorder tiles in a workspace: In the Menu Editing mode, you can reorder tiles in a workspace by dragging each tile to a necessary position.
